form. For example, if we look at something

719
00:45:55,391 --> 00:45:59,974
like this, a centralized layout, we can imagine a number of different

720
00:45:59,974 --> 00:46:04,337
path layouts in it. So we could imagine taking a radial path,

721
00:46:04,337 --> 00:46:09,440
a more grid-like path, or a linear path through that space.

722
00:46:10,325 --> 00:46:15,551
So obviously a linear path through these three different forms, so a linear path that goes

723
00:46:15,551 --> 00:46:22,038
around a centralized form, versus a linear path that goes along a linear form, versus a linear

724
00:46:22,038 --> 00:46:27,064
path that meanders through a clustered form, those linear paths are going to feel very,

725
00:46:27,064 --> 00:46:32,310
very different because of the different forms. And this is because the layout of the form

726
00:46:32,630 --> 00:46:37,474
is dictating our mental model of the space, whereas the layout of the path is dictating

727
00:46:37,474 --> 00:46:43,520
our experience over time. So it's the two of these together which creates the overall structure of

728
00:46:43,520 --> 00:46:49,385
the experience for the player. So there are a few different types of layouts of path,

729
00:46:49,385 --> 00:46:55,430
so just a few examples here. Linear, circular, radial, clustered and grid-like.

730
00:46:57,235 --> 00:47:05,340
So it can be hard to make something that is rich and complex working just from first principles.

731
00:47:05,340 --> 00:47:11,524
So my advice here would be to look at reference and look at perspectival reference as well as

732
00:47:11,524 --> 00:47:17,128
plans and sections. So because you get different information from each of those different types

733
00:47:17,128 --> 00:47:22,871
of reference. Also you're not looking here at the dressing and the details and the textures

734
00:47:22,871 --> 00:47:23,732
and so on.

735
00:47:23,952 --> 00:47:28,715
Instead, you're mentally stripping that away and you're just looking at the spatial design.

736
00:47:28,715 --> 00:47:33,738
And so what you can do is you can look for inspiration here for the kind of experience

737
00:47:33,738 --> 00:47:40,201
you want the player to have and combine that with your direction in terms of the layout of the

738
00:47:40,201 --> 00:47:44,263
space and the layout of the, sorry, the layout of the form and the layout of the player path.

739
00:47:45,683 --> 00:47:48,405
So next under structure, we have intensity.

740
00:47:48,405 --> 00:47:52,529
So it's very important to vary the intensity over the time

741
00:47:52,529 --> 00:47:55,812
because a consistently high level of intensity

742
00:47:55,812 --> 00:47:57,894
will get overwhelming for the player

743
00:47:57,894 --> 00:48:00,497
and a consistently low level will be boring.

744
00:48:00,497 --> 00:48:03,099
So you need to vary your intensity

745
00:48:03,099 --> 00:48:06,082
in order to make a rich experience for the player.

746
00:48:07,120 --> 00:48:11,904
Now, the final intensity that the player experiences will be a mixture.

747
00:48:11,904 --> 00:48:17,528
It will come from a mix of the environment, art, with the gameplay and the narrative.

748
00:48:18,560 --> 00:48:21,922
So you could imagine a situation like here,

749
00:48:21,922 --> 00:48:24,264
where we have a very serene environment,

750
00:48:24,264 --> 00:48:27,286
and it's mixed with incredibly intense gameplay,

751
00:48:27,286 --> 00:48:29,908
and so the player's experience is going to be very intense.

752
00:48:29,908 --> 00:48:33,491
And of course, we could also imagine the reverse,

753
00:48:33,491 --> 00:48:36,813
where you get a very intense environment,

754
00:48:36,813 --> 00:48:38,475
but the gameplay is very calm.

755
00:48:38,475 --> 00:48:42,398
That is still going to result in a more intense experience

756
00:48:42,398 --> 00:48:44,980
than having calm gameplay in a calm environment.

757
00:48:46,129 --> 00:48:49,992
So in terms of where and how we can increase visual intensity,

758
00:48:49,992 --> 00:48:58,297
so we can do that through affinity and contrast. So the more contrast you have in an environment,

759
00:48:58,297 --> 00:49:00,799
the higher the level of intensity will be.

760
00:49:01,671 --> 00:49:03,832
And that's all from this book here.

761
00:49:03,832 --> 00:49:07,053
But we can also increase intensity

762
00:49:07,053 --> 00:49:09,954
just purely in the aesthetics alone.

763
00:49:09,954 --> 00:49:13,815
So we can do things like have more intense colors.

764
00:49:13,815 --> 00:49:15,836
We can have more intense shapes.

765
00:49:15,836 --> 00:49:17,796
So angular shapes and jagged shapes

766
00:49:17,796 --> 00:49:21,077
and things which are unbalanced and top-heavy,

767
00:49:21,077 --> 00:49:23,398
they are going to be more intense

768
00:49:23,398 --> 00:49:25,939
than square shapes and vertical shapes

769
00:49:25,939 --> 00:49:27,720
and things which are very stable.

770
00:49:28,600 --> 00:49:30,681
And of course, increasing density

771
00:49:30,681 --> 00:49:33,163
will increase your intensity as well.

772
00:49:33,163 --> 00:49:35,885
So finally, under structure,

773
00:49:35,885 --> 00:49:38,167
I'm going to talk about contrast.

774
00:49:38,167 --> 00:49:41,830
So as humans, we understand things through contrast.

775
00:49:41,830 --> 00:49:45,072
Somebody is short compared to somebody who is taller.

776
00:49:45,072 --> 00:49:48,454
Somebody is young compared to somebody who is older.

777
00:49:48,454 --> 00:49:50,356
So if we want to communicate

778
00:49:50,356 --> 00:49:53,098
that a particular building is very modern,

779
00:49:53,098 --> 00:49:56,600
if we have that building in a sea of other modern buildings,

780
00:49:56,620 --> 00:50:00,406
that meaning is going to get lost, nobody will notice.

781
00:50:00,406 --> 00:50:03,390
However, if we have our modern building

782
00:50:03,390 --> 00:50:05,493
in a context of buildings which are much older,

783
00:50:05,493 --> 00:50:07,776
then the player will notice.

784
00:50:07,776 --> 00:50:10,320
Now, it sounds very obvious when I say it.

785
00:50:10,838 --> 00:50:12,919
But in practice and in the moment,

786
00:50:12,919 --> 00:50:15,841
this can actually be counterintuitive.

787
00:50:15,841 --> 00:50:17,461
Often the obvious thing to do

788
00:50:17,461 --> 00:50:20,903
always feels like to be consistent.

789
00:50:20,903 --> 00:50:22,884
However, if we're too consistent,

790
00:50:22,884 --> 00:50:25,825
then we lose any contrast

791
00:50:25,825 --> 00:50:28,526
and we lose some of our storytelling for the player.

792
00:50:28,526 --> 00:50:33,929
This isn't just about contrast over a single visual field.

793
00:50:33,929 --> 00:50:36,290
This is about contrast over time.

794
00:50:37,788 --> 00:50:40,591
So there is a concept in environmental psychology

795
00:50:40,591 --> 00:50:44,234
called adaptation, and that's about how we become adapted

796
00:50:44,234 --> 00:50:45,976
to things over time.

797
00:50:45,976 --> 00:50:49,459
So somebody who lives in a busy city will become adapted

798
00:50:49,459 --> 00:50:52,462
to the faster pace of life in that busy city,

799
00:50:52,462 --> 00:50:55,505
and somebody who lives in the countryside will get adapted

800
00:50:55,505 --> 00:50:58,088
to the slower pace of life in the countryside.

801
00:50:58,882 --> 00:51:04,563
So what that means for us, let's say we were going to do a design like this and we wanted

802
00:51:04,563 --> 00:51:11,045
the players to notice how ornamental and intricate and detailed it is. However, if every other space

803
00:51:11,045 --> 00:51:16,826
we've given the player looks like this, the player is going to become adapted to this level of

804
00:51:16,826 --> 00:51:21,887
ornament and detail. And when the player eventually sees this space, they're simply not going to

805
00:51:21,887 --> 00:51:24,088
notice how ornamental it is.

806
00:51:24,687 --> 00:51:29,649
However, if every other space we've given the player beforehand looks like this,

807
00:51:29,649 --> 00:51:34,372
then the player will become adapted to this level of ornament and detail, or lack of it,

808
00:51:34,372 --> 00:51:40,275
and then when the player eventually gets here, it's going to seem incredibly intricate and

809
00:51:40,275 --> 00:51:44,618
ornamental to the player. So to sum up the structure section,

810
00:51:44,618 --> 00:51:50,301
layout was about the layout of the form and the layout of the path.

811
00:51:50,712 --> 00:51:54,977
and the overall player experience comes from a mixture of both.

812
00:51:54,977 --> 00:51:59,181
And with intensity, it's important to vary the intensity over time.

813
00:51:59,181 --> 00:52:04,107
And with contrast, it's important to have contrast in order to communicate to the

814
00:52:04,107 --> 00:52:07,651
player. And to sum up the whole talk now, so the

815
00:52:07,651 --> 00:52:11,976
first section, mimesis, that was all about mimicking and copying

816
00:52:11,976 --> 00:52:12,696
reality.

817
00:52:13,225 --> 00:52:17,252
Semiotics was all about signs and symbols and how we communicate.

818
00:52:17,252 --> 00:52:21,538
The cognition section was all about neuroscience and psychology

819
00:52:21,538 --> 00:52:24,663
and then we ended on some aspects of structure.

820
